(14,10,1,'The Rule of the Square','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The rule of the square will help you calculate faster whether you or your opponent will be able to promote the pawn before the opposing king captures it.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Start by drawing a diagonal arrow from your pawn to the board edge (the red line). Then draw a perfect square around it (the yellow lines).<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The pawn can promote if the opposing king is outside the square and can not get in on the next move. Otherwise, the king will capture the pawn before promotion.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Look at the example below. You can see that the black king is outside the square. If it\'s white\'s turn to move, the pawn will promote. If it\'s black\'s turn to move, black will enter the square on f4 and capture the pawn.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"chess-image\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/1P6\\/6k1\\/8\\/7K w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/1P6\\/6k1\\/8\\/7K w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"39846d70-cbd7-11ec-bdbb-83c5686f7479\",\"firstSquare\":34,\"secondSquare\":2,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"39cd0f30-cbd7-11ec-bdbb-83c5686f7479\",\"firstSquare\":2,\"secondSquare\":6,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"3a1080d0-cbd7-11ec-bdbb-83c5686f7479\",\"firstSquare\":6,\"secondSquare\":38,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"3a61ae10-cbd7-11ec-bdbb-83c5686f7479\",\"firstSquare\":38,\"secondSquare\":34,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"3b80d9b0-cbd7-11ec-bdbb-83c5686f7479\",\"firstSquare\":34,\"secondSquare\":6,\"color\":\"#F46120\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false}],\"movePointer\":0},\"exclude\":[\"right-click\",\"left-click\",\"engine\",\"chessjs