(29,25,1,'Opposition','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Opposition is when one king takes away advancing squares from the opposing king. The side that does not have to move has the opposition.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If the stronger side has the opposition, it will use it to execute an outflank. When the enemy king retreats to one side, our king will advance from the other side.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If the weaker side has the opposition, it will use it to prevent the outflank.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">There are three types of opposition in chess:<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"1\\\"><li>Direct opposition.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":6,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"2\\\"><li>Diagonal opposition.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":7,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"3\\\"><li>Distant opposition.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}]','2022-06-18 07:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:18'),
(30,25,2,'Direct Opposition','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Direct opposition is when the kings are on the same file (column) with one square between them.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Look at the example below. The kings are facing each other with one square between them. Let\'s imagine that the white king wants to enter the fourth rank.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If it\'s black\'s turn to move, white will enter the fourth rank since white has the opposition. When the black king retreats to one side, white will enter the fourth rank from the other side.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul class=\\\"mt-1 mb-2\\\"><li>If it\'s white\'s turn to move, the black king will follow the white king and restrict it from getting on the fourth rank. For example, if white plays Kf3, black will respond with Kf5 and keep the opposition.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"chess-image\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/4k3\\/8\\/4K3\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/4k3\\/8\\/4K3\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false}],\"movePointer\":0},\"exclude\":[\"right-click\",\"left-click\",\"engine\",\"chessjs\"]}}]','2022-06-18 07:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:18'),
