(76,52,1,'Pawn Races','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Pawn races occur when both sides have one or more passed pawns and are trying to be the first to promote to a queen.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">There are a couple of principles that will help you win more often.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"1\\\"><li>Do not move your king on a future checking square of your opponent\'s passed pawn.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"2\\\"><li>Do not waste time capturing unnecessary Pawns.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"3\\\"><li>Do not stop calculating if both Pawns queen simultaneously.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":6,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"4\\\"><li>Use your king to secure your promotion or prevent your opponent\'s promotion.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":7,\"type\":\"warning\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The principles will guide your thinking in the right direction, but don\'t follow them without thinking. Always calculate a few moves ahead. Some positions will require you to break some of these principles.<\\/p>\"}]','2022-07-17 00:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:19'),
(77,52,2,'Do not move your King on a future checking square of your opponent\'s passed Pawn','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">In the example below, if both sides play correctly, the game will end in a draw.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">For the white king, it\'s crucial to avoid the b5 square. If white plays Kb5, black will promote with a check and stop white from promoting. White would lose the game.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Instead, white should clear the way for the pawn and avoid the check by playing Kb4 or Kb3.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/5p2\\/K4k2\\/P7\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/5p2\\/K4k2\\/P7\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[],\"highlightedSquares\":[{\"square\":62,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":44,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":53,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":35,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":26,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":17,\"color\":\"#F46120\"}],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/5p2\\/1K3k2\\/P7\\/8\\/8 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[33,34],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"e583be60-05fb-11ed-a992-61b1ccebeebf\",\"firstSquare\":33,\"secondSquare\":34,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/5p2\\/1K6\\/P3k3\\/8\\/8 w - - 2 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[38,45],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"e6874bb0-05fb-11ed-a992-61b1ccebeebf\",\"firstSquare\":38,\"secondSquare\":45,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/5p2\\/PK6\\/4k3\\/8\\/8 b - - 0 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[41,33],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{