(118,82,1,'Bishop vs. Connected Pawns','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The side with the bishop has to block\\/attack the pawns with the king\\/bishop, while the opponent wants to promote the pawns and win.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">In the example below, white has a few options:<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"1\\\"><li>Kc5 - with the idea to prevent the black king from getting in the corner.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"2\\\" class=\\\"mb-2\\\"><li>Ka5 - with the idea to protect the pawns and promote them.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Depending on white\'s first move, black has to implement a different plan to secure the draw.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":6,\"type\":\"chess-image\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/6k1\\/PK4b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/6k1\\/PK4b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"d7f61c50-1269-11ed-a00a-357fab81b2b0\",\"firstSquare\":34,\"secondSquare\":25,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"d8337370-1269-11ed-a00a-357fab81b2b0\",\"firstSquare\":34,\"secondSquare\":27,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[{\"square\":27,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"square\":25,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"toMove\":\"player\"}],\"movePointer\":0},\"exclude\":[\"right-click\",\"left-click\",\"engine\",\"chessjs\"]}}]','2022-08-05 00:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:20'),
(119,82,2,'Bishop vs. Connected Pawns','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Let\'s first look at the line where white plays Kc5 as the first move. The idea is to give \\\"shouldering\\\" to the opponent\'s king.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Notice the necessary Bd1 move in the example. The bishop is preventing the b-pawn from advancing and attacking the a4 pawn. Once white plays a5, black responds with Be2 controlling both pawns.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"warning\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb=2\\\">It\'s crucial to play Bd1 before Be2. If black plays Be2 directly, white will push the b-pawn to b5. And the b5 pawn will be protected by a4. White will be winning.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/6k1\\/PK4b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/6k1\\/PK4b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/8\\/2K3k1\\/P5b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[34,27],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"461cb300-126b-11ed-8fe0-63afa77a0a07\",\"firstSquare\":34,\"secondSquare\":27,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/5k2\\/2K5\\/P5b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 w - - 2 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[31,22],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"470cdf60-126b-11ed-8fe0-63afa77a0a07\",\"firstSquare\":31,\"secondSquare\":22,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/3K1k2\\/8\\/P5b1\\/8\\/1P6\\/8 b - - 3 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[27,20],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"483aff20-126b-11ed-8fe0-63afa77a0a07\",\"firstSquare\":27,\"secondSquare\":20,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"h