(126,85,4,'Two Connected Pawns','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">When one side has two connected pawns, the only drawing idea for the weaker side is to attack the pawns with the bishop from the front and block them with the king. It\'s crucial to attack them from the front.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Look at the example below. It\'s the ideal drawing position for white.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If the black king moves away from the e5 pawn, the bishop will capture the e5 pawn.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If black pushes to e4, white can play Bd4, and black won\'t be able to improve the position.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ul><li>If black pushes to d4, white can sacrifice the bishop for both pawns and draw (it\'s crucial to attack the pawns with the bishop from the front to achieve this).<\\/li><\\/ul>\"},{\"number\":6,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/8\\/4k3\\/3ppb2\\/8\\/4K3\\/1B6\\/8 b - - 0 1\",\"rotate\":false,\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/4k3\\/3ppb2\\/8\\/4K3\\/1B6\\/8 b - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"441d9020-15b7-11ed-af3c-eb083fe0df21\",\"firstSquare\":50,\"secondSquare\":29,\"color\":\"#F46120\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/4k3\\/4pb2\\/3p4\\/4K3\\/1B6\\/8 w - - 0 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[28,36],\"checkSquare\":45,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"48c630a0-15b7-11ed-af3c-eb083fe0df21\",\"firstSquare\":28,\"secondSquare\":36,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/8\\/4k3\\/4pb2\\/3B4\\/4K3\\/8\\/8 b - - 0 2\",\"sound\":\"capture\",\"lastMoves\":[50,36],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"4a5d2450-15b7-11ed-af