(166,107,5,'Checkmate with Bishop and Knight','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-1 mt-4 font-bold\\\">4. Reposition your bishop and knight to create a wall.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Centralize your knight, which forces the opponent\'s king closer to the desired corner. Position your bishop one square away from the edge of the triangle from the opposite side of your king. In the example below, that square is b3. Once the bishop is in place, position your knight one square away from the bishop on the same colored square as the bishop. That\'s the d3 square.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Notice the wall the pieces create for the opponent\'s king in the final position.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"5k2\\/5N2\\/6K1\\/3B4\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"rotate\":false,\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"5k2\\/5N2\\/6K1\\/3B4\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"e40e7e70-4670-11ed-a186-ff7fec5f1214\",\"firstSquare\":49,\"secondSquare\":7,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"e47c5b70-4670-11ed-a186-ff7fec5f1214\",\"firstSquare\":7,\"secondSquare\":1,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"e4f02be0-4670-11ed-a186-ff7fec5f1214\",\"firstSquare\":1,\"secondSquare\":49,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"5k2\\/8\\/6K1\\/3BN3\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[14,29],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"62b88f10-466f-11ed-a186-ff7fec5f1214\",\"firstSquare\":14,\"secondSquare\":29,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[{\"square\":7,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":14,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"square\":15,\"color\":\"#F46120\"}],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/4k3\\/6K1\\/3BN3\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 2 2\",\"sound\"