(188,122,1,'Rook vs. Rook and Pawn (6th rank)','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">In this lesson, we\'ll look at two different cases for the rook against rook and 6th rank pawn endgames:<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"1\\\"><li>The king of the weaker side is in front of the pawn.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<ol start=\\\"2\\\"><li>The king of the weaker side cut off from the pawn.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}]','2022-10-15 00:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:22'),
(189,122,2,'The King of the weaker side is in front of the Pawn','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Look at the example below. White is winning by moving the rook to a7.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"warning\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">White mustn\'t play Ra1 on the first move and take another route because black can reply with Rh7, and the advantage is lost.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The evaluation of this position is different based on whose turn it\'s to move. If it\'s white to move, white is winning. Otherwise, black can secure the draw. Also, it\'s important to note that if the white king is from the other side of the pawn (d6), the game will end in a draw since black has Rh6+.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"1k5r\\/8\\/1KP5\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/2R5 w - - 0 1\",\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"1k5r\\/8\\/1KP5\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/2R5 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"1k5r\\/8\\/1KP5\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/4R3 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[59,61],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"9491aa20-4bed-11ed-9fb8-9dcee3223568\",\"firstSquare\":59,\"secondSquare\":61,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"1kr5\\/8\\/1KP5\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/4R3 w - - 2 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[8,3],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"9653a570-4bed-11ed-9fb8-9dcee3223568\",\"firstSquare\":8,\"secondSquare\":3,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"1kr5\\/4R3\\/1KP5\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 b - - 3 2\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[61,13],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"9abccbf0-4bed-11ed-9fb8-9dcee3223568\",\"firstSquare\":61,\"secondSquare\":13,\"