(203,127,5,'The knight separated from the king','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">When the knight is at least two moves away from his king, your first goal as the attacker is to trap and win the knight.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p>Ideas that will help you make the right moves when the knight is separated from the king:<\\/p><ol start=\\\"1\\\" class=\\\"mb-2\\\"><li>Position your rook one square away diagonally from the knight. Like this, you control half of the squares the knight can move to.<\\/li><li>Prevent the knight from getting closer to the king.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">In the example below, black wants to get the knight closer to the king. But white can trap the knight with the right moves.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Notice how white pushes the knight closer to the edge and limits the knight\'s mobility.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"8\\/6k1\\/1n6\\/4RK2\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"rotate\":false,\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"8\\/6k1\\/1n6\\/4RK2\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"246c0e10-4cbb-11ed-9ce2-df7c1c5de63d\",\"firstSquare\":18,\"secondSquare\":28,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"id\":\"24dd9490-4cbb-11ed-9ce2-df7c1c5de63d\",\"firstSquare\":18,\"secondSquare\":12,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"id\":\"25468f90-4cbb-11ed-9ce2-df7c1c5de63d\",\"firstSquare\":12,\"secondSquare\":6,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"id\":\"25b33410-4cbb-11ed-9ce2-df7c1c5de63d\",\"firstSquare\":12,\"secondSquare\":22,\"color\":\"#F46120\"},{\"id\":\"2625f310-4cbb-11ed-9ce2-df7c1c5de63d\",\"firstSquare\":28,\"secondSquare\":22,\"color\":\"#F46120\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/6k1\\/1n2K3\\/4R3\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":