(230,149,1,'Queen vs. Rook','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">The queen against a rook checkmate is much more challenging than the queen against a bishop or a knight checkmate.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p>To successfully checkmate your opponent, follow these steps:<\\/p><ol><li>Push the opponent\'s king to the board edge.<\\/li><li>Push the opponent\'s king to the board corner.<\\/li><li>Separate the opponent\'s king and rook.<\\/li><li>Win by forking the king and rook.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"warning\",\"content\":\"<ol><li>Avoid stalemate.<\\/li><li>Do not let your opponent capture your queen.<\\/li><li>Checkmate in less than 50 moves.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}]','2022-10-28 00:00:00','2023-01-30 16:19:24'),
(231,149,2,'King in the corner','[{\"number\":1,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">In the example below, you can see the perfect position for the side with the queen. The opponent\'s king is in the corner, and white\'s goal is to separate the king and rook and win the game.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":2,\"type\":\"info\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Once the defender\'s king and rook get separated, there\'s usually a queen fork in a few moves.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":3,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">It\'s white to move, and the first task for white is to reach the same position, but black to move. White can achieve that with queen triangulation.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":4,\"type\":\"html\",\"content\":\"<p class=\\\"mb-2\\\">Once the same position is reached with black to move, black has no good moves. The rook and the king get separated, and in a few moves, white wins the rook.<\\/p>\"},{\"number\":5,\"type\":\"chess-lesson\",\"content\":{\"position\":\"6k1\\/6r1\\/5K2\\/7Q\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"rotate\":false,\"chessState\":{\"moveHistory\":[{\"fen\":\"6k1\\/6r1\\/5K2\\/7Q\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 0 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[],\"checkSquare\":null,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"854f2940-56f4-11ed-9555-012ece478933\",\"firstSquare\":32,\"secondSquare\":28,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"85ce6b60-56f4-11ed-9555-012ece478933\",\"firstSquare\":28,\"secondSquare\":64,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"},{\"id\":\"86fd2760-56f4-11ed-9555-012ece478933\",\"firstSquare\":64,\"secondSquare\":32,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"player\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"6k1\\/6r1\\/5K2\\/3Q4\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 b - - 1 1\",\"sound\":\"move\",\"lastMoves\":[32,28],\"checkSquare\":7,\"arrows\":[{\"id\":\"714d3e50-56f4-11ed-9555-012ece478933\",\"firstSquare\":32,\"secondSquare\":28,\"color\":\"#EFB701\"}],\"highlightedSquares\":[],\"toMove\":\"engine\",\"newMove\":false},{\"fen\":\"8\\/6rk\\/5K2\\/3Q4\\/8\\/8\\/8\\/8 w - - 2 2